                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d242">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">845.00/1929: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">William Phillips</persName>,
                        Personal Representative of President Roosevelt in India, to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">New Delhi</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-04-25T15:00:00+06:30"
                            >April 25, 1943—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received April 25—8:21 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>307. During the last 2 days I have been visiting the Viceroy at a shooting camp
                    and have discussed all angles of the Indian situation.</p>
                <p>With his consent I am saying this afternoon at a press conference of the Indian
                    and American correspondents that naturally I should like to have met and talked
                    with Mr. Gandhi; that I have requested the appropriate authorities for
                    permission to do so and have been informed that they were unable to grant the
                    necessary facilities.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
